      "lesson title": "Ransomware and AI in Healthcare Systems",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "As healthcare organisations increasingly rely on artificial intelligence to support clinical decision-making, diagnostics, and patient management, the threat of ransomware has become far more serious than ever before. When cybercriminals target AI-driven systems, the disruption can cascade rapidly across an entire organisation, affecting everything from automated medication dispensing to real-time patient monitoring. This lesson introduces the fundamentals of ransomware, explores how it interacts with AI-powered healthcare infrastructure, and explains why the consequences of an attack in this environment can be so severe. No prior technical knowledge is required, and the content is designed to give healthcare professionals a clear and practical understanding of the risks they face. By the end of this lesson, you will be better equipped to recognise vulnerabilities, understand the potential impact on patient safety, and appreciate why protecting these systems is a critical priority for every member of a healthcare team.",
